# Designing a model
model = Sequential()  
# Input Layer
model.add(Dense(128, activation = 'relu', kernel_initializer = 'normal',input_dim = X_train_s.shape[1]))
# Adding the hidden layers
model.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer = 'normal'))
model.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer = 'normal'))
model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha = 0.1))
model.add(Dense(16, kernel_initializer = 'normal'))
model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha = 0.1))
# Adding the Output Layer
model.add(Dense(9, kernel_initializer = 'normal', activation = 'softmax'))
# Compiling the model
model.compile(loss = 'mean_absolute_error', optimizer = 'adam', metrics = ['accuracy'])
model.summary()

# Adding Batch Normalization to try to improve the model
model2 = Sequential()
# Input Layer
model2.add(Dense(128, activation = 'relu', kernel_initializer = 'normal', input_dim = X_train_s.shape[1]))
model2.add(BatchNormalization())

# Adding the hidden layers
model2.add(Dense(64, kernel_initializer = 'normal'))
model2.add(LeakyReLU(alpha = 0.1))
model2.add(BatchNormalization())

model2.add(Dense(32, kernel_initializer = 'normal'))
model2.add(LeakyReLU(alpha = 0.1))
model2.add(BatchNormalization())

model2.add(Dense(16, kernel_initializer = 'normal'))
model2.add(LeakyReLU(alpha = 0.1))
model2.add(BatchNormalization())

# Adding the Output Layer
model2.add(Dense(9, kernel_initializer = 'normal', activation = 'softmax'))

# Compiling the model
model2.compile(loss = 'mean_absolute_error', optimizer = 'adam', metrics = ['accuracy'])
model2.summary()
